# MS Teams / Azure AD Configuration
# To enable MS Teams integration, you'll need to:
# 1. Register an application in Azure AD
# 2. Configure the redirect URI to match your application URL
# 3. Grant the necessary Microsoft Graph permissions
# 4. Copy the Client ID here

NEXT_PUBLIC_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-client-id-here

# Instructions for setting up Azure AD App Registration:
# 1. Go to https://portal.azure.com
# 2. Navigate to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
# 3. Click "New registration"
# 4. Name: "Onboarding App Teams Integration"
# 5. Supported account types: "Accounts in any organizational directory"
# 6. Redirect URI: Web - http://localhost:3000 (or your production URL)
# 7. After creation, copy the "Application (client) ID"
# 8. Go to "API permissions" and add:
#    - Microsoft Graph > Delegated permissions:
#      - Files.Read.All
#      - Sites.Read.All
#      - Group.Read.All
#      - Channel.ReadBasic.All
# 9. Click "Grant admin consent" if you have admin privileges
# 10. Paste the Client ID above and rename this file to .env.local